descript.abstract: This layer contains data from the Geographic Names Information System (GNIS) which was developed by the USGS "to meet major national needs regarding geographic names and their standardization and dissemination". The data consist of point locations with corresponding feature names. All point entities are categorized by feature type. This data is representative of dam locations found in the general GNIS data set.
descript.supplinf:
Procedures_Used: The original GNIS tabular data were converted by AGRC into INFO format and used to generate point locations. The locations in this dataset were originally in geographic format (degrees, minutes, seconds). These were projected into UTM coordinate values.
Reviews_Applied_to_Data: Visual check was performed to confirm the conversion process.
Related_Spatial_and_Tabular_Data_Sets: An INFO file is related on the CODE item describing the feature type. Named GFNAM.CODE, this file can be found in the QU100/TABLES directory.
